{{Infobox road |country = MKD |type = A |route = 2 |map_notes= |e-road = [[European route E65|E65]] |length_km= 73 |direction_a=East |terminus_a= [[Skopje]] Airport |junction= |direction_b=West |terminus_b= [[Tetovo]] |cities= [[Skopje]], [[Tetovo]] }}
The '''A2''' motorway ({{lang-mk|'''A2 автопат'''}}) is a national motorway in the [[Republic of Macedonia]]. It forms part of the [[European route E65]] (E65), connecting the cities of [[Skopje]] and [[Tetovo]].
==Route== Beginning from the [[Skopje]] airport interchange of the [[A1 Motorway (Republic of Macedonia)|A1 Motorway]], it connects the aforementioned motorway with the city of [[Tetovo]], forming a partial [[beltway]] around [[Skopje]]. The Skopje beltway is also part of the [[M-4 Motorway (FYROM)|M-4 Motorway]], which follows another route thereafter. Leaving Skopje, it continues to [[Tetovo]]. [[Gostivar]] is about 19&nbsp;km south and it can be easily reached, using the [[Controlled-access highway|expressway]] part of the road. This part is just like the rest of the A2, but it does not feature an emergency lane and it does not meet some other motorway requirements.
==Pictures== <gallery> Skopskipat.jpg|The A2 outside [[Skopje]] </gallery>
==Future plans== The existing [[Kičevo]] - [[Ohrid]] [[single carriageway]] road will be turned into a motorway with 4 traffic lanes. This section is currently under construction. After completion, it will form part of the A2.
