The '''Amphitheatre of Libarna''' is found in the ancient Roman city of Libarna, near the modern town of [[Serravalle Scrivia]], in [[Piedmont]].  It was discovered in excavations throughout the 20th century alongside remains of bath buildings.<ref>[http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.04.0006:entry=libarna The Princeton Encyclopedia of Classical Sites]</ref>

