The '''Constitution of the Cisalpine Republic''' ({{lang-it|Costituzione della Repubblica Cisalpina}}), was the second [[constitution]] of the [[Cisalpine Republic]], a [[Sister Republic]] of [[First French Republic|France]] under [[Napoleon|Napoleon Bonaparte]], roughly comprising the modern-day [[Northern Italy|northern]] [[Regions of Italy|region]]s of [[Lombardy]] and [[Emilia-Romagna]]. It came into effect on 31 August 1798, replacing the [[Constitution of the Cisalpine Republic (1797)|1797 Constitution]].
