'''''Demokraatti''''' is a [[Finnish language]] newspaper and [[Social Democratic Party of Finland|Social Democratic Party]] organ published daily in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]. 

==History and profile==
''Demokraatti'' was established in 1895. The paper is headquartered in Helsinki<ref>{{cite web|title=Finland country profile|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-17290044|work=BBC|accessdate=8 January 2015|date=7 March 2012}}</ref> and is the organ of the [[Social Democratic Party of Finland|Social Democratic Party]].<ref name=rai>{{cite web|author=Raimo Salokangas|title=From Political to National, Regional and Local|url=http://web.iaincirebon.ac.id/ebook/moon/LocalMatters/31_salokangas.pdf|publisher=Cirebon|accessdate=14 December 2014|format=Book chapter|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214172635/http://web.iaincirebon.ac.id/ebook/moon/LocalMatters/31_salokangas.pdf|archivedate=14 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=M. W. Bauer|author2=G. Gaskell|title=Biotechnology - the Making of a Global Controversy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gXK4kGXZgSQC&pg=PA342|accessdate=8 January 2015|date=5 September 2002|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-77439-0|page=342}}</ref> The paper is published five times a week.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Jyrki Jyrkiäinen|title=Newspaper Chains in Finland 1993–2010|journal=Journal of Media Business Studies|date=2009|volume=9|issue=2|doi=10.1080/16522354.2012.11073541|url=https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/16522354.2012.11073541|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref> In late 1997 another social democratic paper, ''[[Turun Päivälehti]]'', merged with ''Demokraatti'', and they began to publish the same material, although ''Turun Päivälehti'' preserved its name.<ref name=rai/>

The circulation of ''Demokraatti'' was 25,000 copies in 1997.<ref name=rai/>

