{{Infobox artwork | title = Girl in a White Kimono | image_file = George Hendrik Breitner - Meisje in witte kimono (Geesje Kwak).jpg | caption = | painting_alignment = | image_size = 300 | alt = | other_language_1 = [[Dutch language|Dutch]] | other_title_1 = Meisje in witte kimono | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[George Hendrik Breitner]] | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1894}} | material = [[Oil on canvas]] | subject = Geesje Kwak | height_metric = 59 | width_metric = 57 | length_metric = | dimensions = | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | condition = | city = [[Amsterdam]] | museum = [[Rijksmuseum]] | accession = | owner = | url = <!--{{URL|example.com}} Only for official web pages--> }}
'''''Girl in a White Kimono''''' ({{lang-nl|Meisje in witte kimono}}) is an 1894 [[oil painting]] by [[George Hendrik Breitner]].<ref name="rijksmuseum">[https://www.rijksmuseum.nl/en/search/objecten?q=SK-A-3584#/SK-A-3584,0 Girl in a White Kimono, George Hendrik Breitner, 1894], [[Rijksmuseum]]. Retrieved on 2 May 2014.</ref> The subject of the painting is the sixteen-year-old Geesje Kwak, of whom Breitner made a series of photographs and paintings wearing red and white [[kimono]]s.<ref>{{nl icon}} [http://explore.rkd.nl/nl/explore/artists/433934 Geesje Kwak], [[Netherlands Institute for Art History]], 2012. Retrieved on 2 May 2014.</ref> The painting was inspired by the style of Japanese prints and is an example of [[Japonism]].<ref>[http://www.christies.com/lotfinder/lot/george-hendrik-breitner-meisje-in-rode-kimono-4168796-details.aspx?intObjectID=4168796 Lot Notes], [[Christie's]]. Retrieved on 2 May 2014.</ref> The painting is in the collection of the [[Rijksmuseum]] in [[Amsterdam]].<ref name="rijksmuseum"/>
