{{Infobox mountain | name = Grand Tavé | photo = Corbassiere2.JPG | photo_caption = Grand Tavé (left summit) from the [[Corbassière Glacier]] | elevation_m = 3158 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 40 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps and [[Google Earth]]. The key col is located south of the summit at 3,118 metres.</ref> | parent_peak = [[Tavé des Chasseurs]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Pennine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|45|59|36|N|7|18|52|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Grand Tavé''' (3,158 m) is a [[mountain]] of the Swiss [[Pennine Alps]], located south of [[Fionnay]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. It belongs to the [[Grand Combin]] massif and lies east of the [[Corbassière Glacier]].
It lies just south of the Col des Otannes (2,846 m), from where the summit is usually reached.
