'''Leib-Olmai''' ("alder man") is a good [[luck]] god in [[Sami mythology]] who was honoured by the [[Sami people|Sami]].  He lives in the trees of [[Alder]] and gives good luck to hunters against [[bear]]s, and he appears to humans in the form of a bear.  In honour of Leib-Olmai, at bears feasts the hunters' faces were sprinkled with a brownish-red mixture of ground-up [[alder]] bark and water.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.probertencyclopaedia.com/cgi-bin/res.pl?keyword=Leib-Olmai&offset=0I|title= The Probert Encyclopaedia of Enochian Mythology|accessdate=2008-10-01}}</ref>

