{{Infobox Historic Site | name=St. Anthony Church | native_name = Kisha e Shna Ndout | native_language = sq | image =Kisha e Shna Ndout në Laç.jpg | caption =The church in a 2012 picture | designation1 = Cultural Monument of Albania | designation1_date = | designation1_partof = | location = [[Laç]], [[Albania]] | built = 1300<ref name="Merlika"/> | architect = | coordinates = {{coord|41|38|7|N|19|42|47|E|type:adm1st_region:AL_dim:100000|display=inline}} | locmapin = }} The '''St. Anthony Church''' ''({{lang-sq|Kisha e Shna Ndout or Kisha e Laçit}})'', is a 13th century church in the Albanian town of [[Laç]].<ref name="Marku">{{citenews|last1=Marku|first1=Kastriot|title=KISHA E SHNA NDOJIT (SHËN ANTONIT TË PADOVËS) NË LAÇ TË KURBINIT, MONUMENT I ARKITEKTURËS SË SHPRESËS DHE I SFIDËS NDAJ DIKTATURËS|url=http://gazeta55.al/kisha-e-shna-ndojit-shen-antonit-te-padoves-ne-lac-te-kurbinit-monument-i-arkitektures-se-shpreses-dhe-i-sfides-ndaj-diktatures/|accessdate=21 September 2017|agency=Gazeta 55}}</ref><ref name="Merlika">{{cite news |last1=Merlika |first1=Eugjen |title=Historia e Kishës së Laçit! Shenjti portugez i shqiptarëve |url=http://www.mapo.al/historia-e-kishes-se-lacit-shenjti-portugez-i-shqiptareve/ |accessdate=9 November 2018 |agency=Mapo |date=13 June 2015}}</ref>
==History== The church was first built around year 1300, and dedicated to [[St. Mary]], then renamed after [[Anthony of Padua]] in 1557. In 1971 it was destroyed by the [[Communist Albania|communist regime]], and eventually was rebuilt in the 1990s. It is a [[Franciscans|Franciscan]] church..<ref name="Marku"/> Many renowned clergy have served in the church, including [[Shtjefën Gjeçovi]], [[Vinçens Prennushi]], Klement Miraj, Robert Ashta, and [[Zef Pllumi]].<ref name="Merlika"/>
